  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Fix Navigation Menu Visibility and Layout Issues\n\nResolve two issues with the navigation menu: incorrect default visibility state and misaligned layout with the logo.\n\nRequirements:\n- Remove or conditionally apply the 'collapse' class from the menu element so it is visible by default on appropriate screen sizes\n- Adjust the layout/flexbox properties to align the menu horizontally inline with the logo\n- Ensure the menu and logo appear on the same horizontal line in the header\n- Verify responsive behavior: collapsed menu should only apply on mobile/smaller viewports if using a hamburger menu pattern\n- Test that the menu remains accessible and functional after changes\n- Confirm styling is consistent with the overall header design\n\nEdge Cases to Consider:\n- Menu visibility at different viewport breakpoints\n- Menu behavior when toggled on mobile devices (if applicable)\n- Proper alignment regardless of logo size or menu item count",
